Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you donâ€™t have symptoms.

Palau has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Palau, see Return to the UK
There is widespread disruption on international travel routes to Palau. You should check with your travel provider for updates.
Travel restrictions banning travel into Palau for travellers who have travelled from or transited through mainland China, Macao or Hong Kong in the past 14 days are in place.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
